    "recap_headline": "University of Alabama at Birmingham Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BIRMINGHAM\n\u2013 Belmont used a 6-run sixth inning to take down UAB (11-8) by a score of 10-4 on Saturday afternoon. The Bruins (8-11) blasted three home runs in the inning.\nBelmont got the scoring started in the top half of the third inning when 9-hole hitter Michael Lereau hit his first home run of the season. Later in the inning, Jake Maddox singled home Charlie Davis to give Belmont a 2-0 advantage through three innings.\nAfter a UAB pitching change, the Bruins immediately put up two more runs in the top of the fourth. Charlie Davis tripled to right center to drive in those two runs and put BU up, 4-0.\nThe Blazers scored their first run of the day in odd fashion.\nKevin Hall Jr.\nhit a sac fly to the second baseman who caught a pop up behind first base.\nLandon Beaver\ndashed home to cut the Belmont lead to 4-1.\nBrady Waugh\ngot the Blazers closer in the bottom of the fifth. Waugh pushed across two more on a single and a Belmont error to bring around\nAlex Dupuy\nand\nAndrew Hunt\nto cut the Bruins' lead to one.\nThen came Belmont's big inning as it sent 10 hitters to the plate in the frame. The Bruins homered three times thanks to Nate Webb (pinch hitter), Charlie Davis, and Cavan McMeans.\nThe Blazers got a single tally in the bottom of the ninth by way of\nAndrew Hunt's\nsecond home run of the season, but it wasn't enough as Belmont took the middle game of the series, 10-4.\nNOTES\n-\nJustin Hicks\ncame on in relief and tied his career-high with 3.1 innings, good for his longest scoreless outing of his career.\n-\nAlex Dupuy\ntallied his team-leading ninth multi-hit game of the season.\n-\nBrady Waugh\nis now tied for second on the team after his sixth multi-hit game. Waugh also carries a 12-game on-base streak into Sunday.\n-\nWesley Helms\npicked up his second 3-hit game of 2026 and his fifth multi-hit game.\n- In his last at-bat,\nBaylor Roberts\nextended his hit streak to nine games.\n-\nAndrew Hunt\nrecorded his eighth career game in which he scored twice.\nUAB and Belmont square off in the rubber game of the series on Sunday. First pitch from Young Memorial Field is set for 1 p.m. on ESPN+.\nFOLLOW THE BLAZERS\nFor more information on the UAB Baseball team, follow @UAB_Baseball on X and Instagram.\nCompetitive Excellence Fund\nIn the current landscape of college athletics, the Competitive Excellence Fund has become integral in our department's mission to Win Champions, Graduate with Honors, and Impact the community. Through your generosity, our coaches will have the greatest opportunity to recruit, retain, and resource talented student athletes worthy of wearing a UAB uniform.\nClick here\nor connect with Blazer Boosters on how you can continue to fuel success."
